<p class="indent1" style="-uslm-lc:I12" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">The term “active duty” means “active duty” as described in paragraph (21) of <ref href="/us/usc/t38/s101">section 101 of title 38</ref>, United States Code, except that it shall also include “active duty for training” as described in paragraph (22) of such section.</p>
